- `(?<=\/\/)` is a positive lookbehind assertion that matches the sequence `://` from the left.
- `[^\/]+` matches one or more characters that are not a forward slash.
- `(?=\/|$)` is a positive lookahead assertion that matches a forward slash or the end of the string from the right.

